@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Gruer's Story - Gruers Bakery";
}

<div class="container my-5">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-lg-8 col-md-10">

            <!-- Warm, intimate header -->
            <div class="text-center mb-5" data-aos="fade-up">
                <i class="bi bi-chat-heart-fill display-1 text-warm"></i>
                <h1 class="display-4 mt-3" style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; color: var(--wood-dark);">
                    A Letter from Gruer
                </h1>
                <div class="honey-accent mx-auto" style="width: 60px;"></div>
                <p class="text-muted mt-3 small">
                    <i class="bi bi-clock me-1"></i> Late evening, after the last loaf left the oven
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- The Story - Like sitting across from Gruer -->
            <div class="warm-card p-4 p-md-5" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">
                <div class="story-text" style="font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8;">
                    
                    <p class="lead fst-italic text-warm mb-4">
                        "Pull up a chair. Let me tell you something..."
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        I close my eyes sometimes… just to feel it again.
                        The smell of warm bread. The sound of ovens breathing.
                        It's not just memory. It's home.
                    </p>

                    <p class="mt-4">
                        You want to know how Gruer's began?
                        It wasn't a business plan. It wasn't a loan.
                        It was a dream I couldn't stop dreaming.
                    </p>

                    <div class="my-4 text-center">
                        <i class="bi bi-egg-fried text-warm" style="font-size: 2rem; opacity: 0.5;"></i>
                    </div>

                    <p>
                        I see it clearly now. A shop. But not just any shop.
                        Warm wood under your hands. Stone that holds the heat of the day.
                        Light that does not blind you — it welcomes you.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        And the ovens… ah, the ovens.
                        I wanted them visible. No secrets.
                        Let people see the fire that creates what they eat.
                    </p>

                    <p class="fst-italic text-warm my-4">
                        "Because bread is not made in silence… it is made in truth."
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        But there is more… always more.
                        Light that feels almost impossible.
                        Gold… amber… soft as morning honey.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        Plants that don't belong anywhere I know —
                        yet somehow feel like they have always been here.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        A place that feels like home… but also like somewhere you have never been before.
                    </p>

                    <p class="fst-italic text-warm my-4">
                        "That is what I wanted. Not perfection. Feeling."
                    </p>

                    <div class="my-4 text-center">
                        <i class="bi bi-cup-straw text-warm" style="font-size: 2rem; opacity: 0.5;"></i>
                    </div>

                    <p>
                        Behind the counter… dark wood. Solid. Honest.
                        Behind it… the ovens. Alive. Burning gently like a heartbeat.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        And the pastries… not just food…
                        but small stories you can hold in your hands.
                        Stories of mornings. Stories of love. Stories of home.
                    </p>

                    <p class="fst-italic text-warm my-4">
                        "If I can make you feel something when you take a bite… then I have done my job."
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        So that's what we do here. Every day. Every loaf. Every pastry.
                        We don't just bake. We welcome you home.
                    </p>

                    <p class="text-end mt-5 pt-3" style="border-top: 1px solid rgba(245, 197, 66, 0.3);">
                        <span style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-size: 1.2rem;">— Gruer</span>
                        <br>
                        <small class="text-muted">Founder & Head Baker</small>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Invitation -->
            <div class="text-center mt-4" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="200">
                <a asp-area="Admin" asp-controller="Catalog" asp-action="Index" class="btn-warm">
                    <i class="bi bi-house-heart me-2"></i> Visit the Bakery
                </a>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<style>
    .story-text p {
        margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
        color: var(--text-color);
    }
    
    .story-text .lead {
        font-size: 1.3rem;
    }
    
    .text-warm {
        color: var(--honey-gold);
    }
    

</style>

<script>
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
        console.log('📖 Gruer shares his story...');
        
        // Gentle fade-in for paragraphs
        const paragraphs = document.querySelectorAll('.story-text p');
        paragraphs.forEach((p, index) => {
            p.style.opacity = '0';
            p.style.transform = 'translateY(10px)';
            p.style.transition = 'opacity 0.5s ease, transform 0.5s ease';
            setTimeout(() => {
                p.style.opacity = '1';
                p.style.transform = 'translateY(0)';
            }, 100 + (index * 80));
        });
    });
</script>